title: Front Cover
content: A group of Texas Fatmuckets (Lampsilis bracteata) from the Llano River located on the Edwards Plateau of Central Texas, USA. The cover image relates to Research Article [https://doi.org/10.1002/aqc.4224] “Growth and longevity of two imperiled mussel species from the Edwards Plateau of Central Texas and its implications for freshwater mussel conservation and management” by de Moulpied et al. Photo credit: Clint Robertson.
